   "source": [
    "(generalised_filtering)=\n",
    "# Generalised Bayesian Filtering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "6e337fd3-5a3e-4e0f-ab4f-e055cebfb7ff",
   "metadata": {

    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import jax.numpy as jnp\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm, t\n",
    "from scipy.special import gammaln\n",
    "from matplotlib.ticker import MultipleLocator\n",
    "from pyhgf.networks import beliefs_propagation\n",
    "from pyhgf.math import SufficientStatistics\n",
    "import jax.numpy as jnp\n",
    "from pyhgf.model import HGF\n",
    "\n",
    "np.random.seed(123)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c9cfc583-b824-4495-8b41-e1a12da04831",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "source": [
    "Here, using the approach described in {cite:p}`weber:2020`we demonstrate how the Hierarchical Gaussian Filter can be generalized to any probability distribution that belongs to the [exponential family](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponential_family).\n",
    "Exponential families of probability distributions are those which can be written in the form:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "p(x|\\nu) = f_x(\\nu) := h(x) exp(\\eta(\\nu) · t(x) − b(\\nu))\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "where:\n",
    "- $x$ is a vector-valued observation\n",
    "- $\\nu$ is a parameter vector\n",
    "- $h(x)$ is a normalization constant\n",
    "- $\\eta(\\nu)$ is the natural parameter vector\n",
    "- $t(x)$ is the sufficient statistic vector\n",
    "- $b(\\nu)$ is a scalar function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "47a7193b-55f8-415c-8dfb-29f13598fb29",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = np.arange(-15, 15, .01)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "e44a74a7-13b1-41c9-8501-846def16aff5",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def gaussian_predictive_distribution(x, xi, nu):\n",
    "    return (\n",
    "        np.sqrt(1/(np.pi * (nu + 1) * (xi[1] - xi[0]**2)))\n",
    "        * np.exp((gammaln((nu+2) / 2) - gammaln((nu + 1) / 2)))  # use gammaln to avoid numerical overflow\n",
    "        * (1 + ((x-xi[0])**2) / ((nu + 1)*(xi[1]-xi[0]**2)))**(-(nu+2)/2)\n",
    "    )"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "add927a3-4233-484d-ad01-74ad03b87b5b",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },

      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "_, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 3))\n",
    "ax.plot(\n",
    "    x,\n",
    "    gaussian_predictive_distribution(x, xi=np.array([0, 1]), nu=10),\n",
    "    linestyle=\"--\",\n",
    "    label=\"Posterior predictive distribution\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.plot(\n",
    "    x,\n",
    "    t.pdf(x, 11),\n",
    "    linestyle=\":\",\n",
    "    label=\"Student's t distribution\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.xaxis.set_minor_locator(MultipleLocator(1))\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_minor_locator(MultipleLocator(.02))\n",
    "ax.set_title(\"Posterior predictive distribution\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "ax.grid(linestyle=\"--\");\n",
    "sns.despine()"
   ]
  },

    "## Filtering of Sufficient Statistics for Stationary Input Distributions"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "8dc71c6d-e65f-476b-ad88-1a2d4e114bc0",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "xs = np.random.normal(5, 1/4, 1000)  # inputs\n",
    "\n",
    "# initial parameters\n",
    "xi = np.array([0, 1/8])\n",
    "nu = 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "ba318975-ce19-4b47-9934-bd02c0130e10",
   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 3))\n",
    "plt.plot(\n",
    "    x, \n",
    "    gaussian_predictive_distribution(x, xi=xi, nu=nu), \n",
    "    color=\"k\",\n",
    "    label=\"Prior\",\n",
    "    linestyle=\"--\"\n",
    ");\n",
    "for i, x_i in enumerate(xs):\n",
    "    xi = xi + (1/(1+nu)) * (SufficientStatistics.normal(x_i) - xi)\n",
    "    nu += 1\n",
    "\n",
    "    if i in [2, 4, 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256, 512, 999]:\n",
    "        plt.plot(\n",
    "            x, \n",
    "            gaussian_predictive_distribution(x, xi=xi, nu=nu), \n",
    "            color=\"grey\",\n",
    "            linewidth=1.0\n",
    "        );\n",
    "plt.plot(\n",
    "    x, \n",
    "    norm.pdf(x, loc=5.0, scale=1/4), \n",
    "    color=\"#582766\",\n",
    "    label=\"Target distribution\"\n",
    ");\n",
    "plt.xlim(-2, 7)\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(linestyle=\"--\");\n",
    "sns.despine()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "## Filtering of Sufficient Statistics for Non-stationary Input Distributions\n",
    "### Using a fixed $\\nu$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 75,
   "id": "2d921e51-a940-42b2-88f2-e25bd7ab5a01",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = np.arange(0, 1000)\n",
    "\n",
    "# create noisy input time series\n",
    "xs = np.random.normal(0, 1/8, 1000)\n",
    "xs[200:400] += .5\n",
    "xs[600:800] -= .5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 76,
   "id": "1ee325b1-7cc1-44fe-a193-5f337a9cd9e9",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# initialize nu at different values\n",
    "nu_1, nu_2 = 3, 20\n",
    "xi_1, xi_2 = np.array([0, 1/8]), np.array([0, 1/8])\n",
    "\n",
    "xis = []\n",
    "for i, x_i in enumerate(xs):\n",
    "    xi_1 = xi_1 + (1/(1+nu_1)) * (SufficientStatistics.normal(x_i) - xi_1)\n",
    "    xi_2 = xi_2 + (1/(1+nu_2)) * (SufficientStatistics.normal(x_i) - xi_2)\n",
    "    xis.append((xi_1, xi_2))\n",
    "xis = np.asarray(xis)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 77,
   "id": "0754380d-87d0-430e-a533-540c5f252091",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "_, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\n",
    "ax.scatter(x, xs, color=\"grey\", alpha=.6, s=10);\n",
    "ax.plot(x, xis[:, 0, 0], label=rf\"$\\nu = {nu_1}$\")\n",
    "ax.plot(x, xis[:, 1, 0], label=rf\"$\\nu = {nu_2}$\")\n",
    "ax.grid(linestyle=\"--\");\n",
    "ax.set_title(r\"Filtering sufficient statistics using a fixed $\\nu$\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Observations\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "sns.despine()"
   ]

   "source": [
    "### Filtering $\\nu$ with Hierarchical Gaussian Filter"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 78,
   "id": "baf6e2fc-dc8d-46bb-896b-ff5c45a944ee",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initializing a network with custom node structure.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "general_filter_hgf = (\n",
    "    HGF(model_type=None)\n",
    "    .add_nodes(kind=\"continuous-input\", node_parameters={\"input_precision\": 100})\n",
    "    .add_nodes(value_children=0, node_parameters={\"tonic_volatility\": -6.0})\n",
    "    .add_nodes(volatility_children=[1], node_parameters={\"mean\": 0, \"tonic_volatility\": -2})\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 79,
   "id": "f7a6c0da-934f-4782-af6b-6b5ad2e94c02",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""
    },
    "tags": []
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "general_filter_hgf.set_update_sequence()\n",
    "attributes = general_filter_hgf.attributes\n",
    "\n",
    "nus = []\n",
    "for i, x_i in enumerate(xs):\n",
    "    mean = attributes[1][\"mean\"]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    attributes, _ = beliefs_propagation(\n",
    "        edges=general_filter_hgf.edges,\n",
    "        attributes=attributes,\n",
    "        input_data=(x_i, [1.0], 1.0),\n",
    "        input_nodes_idx=general_filter_hgf.input_nodes_idx.idx,\n",
    "        update_sequence=general_filter_hgf.update_sequence,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    new_mean = attributes[1][\"mean\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "    nus.append(((x_i - mean) / (new_mean - mean)) - 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 80,
   "id": "45cdf250-5a7c-4dc3-b5e7-46055cb35adf",
   "metadata": {
    "editable": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": ""

   ],
   "source": [
    "_, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 3))\n",
    "ax.plot(x, nus, label=rf\"Implied $\\nu$\")\n",
    "ax.grid(linestyle=\"--\");\n",
    "ax.set_title(r\"Implied $\\nu$ parameter by the HGF learning rate\")\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(r\"$\\nu$\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Observations\")\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "sns.despine()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Filtering a bivariate normal distribution"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 143,
   "id": "781b08fc-a2c7-4856-a103-beffd7787325",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# simulate a spiral data set\n",
    "N = 1000\n",
    "theta = np.sort(np.sqrt(np.random.rand(N)) * 5 * np.pi)\n",
    "r_a = -2 * theta - np.pi\n",
    "input_data = np.array([np.cos(theta)*r_a, np.sin(theta)*r_a]).T\n",
    "input_data = input_data + np.random.randn(N,2) * .5"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 145,
   "id": "f5f51a03-d22b-48d5-a3a5-1f913fa0926a",

    "ax.scatter(\n",
    "    input_data[:,0],\n",
    "    input_data[:,1],\n",
    "    edgecolor=\"k\",\n",
    "    alpha=.4,\n",
    "    s=15\n",
    ")\n",
    "ax.grid(linestyle=\"--\");\n",
    "ax.set_title(r\"Filtering a bivariate stochastic process\")\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(r\"$x_1$\")\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 146,
   "id": "ea1ce29f-dd89-44cb-aabd-6d93ecbf128b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sufficient_statistics = jnp.apply_along_axis(\n",
    "    SufficientStatistics.multivariate_normal,\n",
    "    1,\n",
    "    input_data\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 147,
   "id": "d4ac6695-29c0-4ed4-b079-ddf073bac272",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Initializing a network with custom node structure.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "bivariater_hgf = (\n",
    "    HGF(model_type=None)\n",
    "    .add_nodes(\n",
    "        kind=\"continuous-input\", \n",
    "        node_parameters={\"input_precision\": 100.0}, n_nodes=5\n",
    "    )\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(5):\n",
    "    bivariater_hgf.add_nodes(\n",
    "        value_children=i, \n",
    "        node_parameters={\n",
    "            \"tonic_volatility\": -2.0,\n",
    "            \"mean\": sufficient_statistics[0][i],\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(5):\n",
    "    bivariater_hgf.add_nodes(volatility_children=[i+5], node_parameters={\"mean\": 10, \"tonic_volatility\": -2})"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "nus = []\n",
    "for i in range(input_data.shape[0]):\n",
    "    mean = jnp.array([attributes[i][\"mean\"] for i in range(5, 10)])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    attributes, _ = beliefs_propagation(\n",
    "        edges=bivariater_hgf.edges,\n",
    "        attributes=attributes,\n",
    "        input_data=(sufficient_statistics[i], jnp.ones(5), jnp.ones(5)),\n",
    "        input_nodes_idx=bivariater_hgf.input_nodes_idx.idx,\n",
    "        update_sequence=bivariater_hgf.update_sequence,\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    new_mean = jnp.array([attributes[i][\"mean\"] for i in range(5, 10)])\n",
    "\n",
    "    nus.append(((sufficient_statistics[i] - mean) / (new_mean - mean)) - 1)\n",
    "nus = jnp.array(nus)"
   ]
  },

    "\n",

    "def update(frame):\n",
    "    # update the scatter plot:\n",
    "    scat.set_offsets(input_data[:frame])\n",
    "    return scat\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
